1
00:00:02,410 --> 00:00:05,790
One Year Ago

2
00:00:09,980 --> 00:00:17,950
Timing and Subtitles by the Sing To Me Team @ viki

3
00:00:53,600 --> 00:00:57,400
Asia Philharmonic Orchestra &
Kim Ian - Chopin Piano Concerto

4
00:00:58,300 --> 00:01:00,600
Episode 9

5
00:01:00,600 --> 00:01:07,900
Conductor, do you know this person?

6
00:01:08,900 --> 00:01:12,150
What is your real purpose?

7
00:01:12,150 --> 00:01:16,740
You're impersonating someone who died. Why have you shown up here?

8
00:01:16,740 --> 00:01:19,770
A dead person? Who?

9
00:01:28,330 --> 00:01:30,000
Who?

10
00:01:31,100 --> 00:01:34,160
Then why are you so interested in me?

11
00:01:34,900 --> 00:01:38,270
Who are you worried about? What are you so scared of?

12
00:01:38,270 --> 00:01:40,000
Can I look into it?

13
00:01:40,960 --> 00:01:44,460
I can tell everyone that your name is fake.

14
00:01:44,460 --> 00:01:48,030
Tell them if you can. Can you do it?

15
00:01:49,480 --> 00:01:51,270
Don't you know

16
00:01:53,570 --> 00:01:55,340
Kim Ian?

17
00:02:10,760 --> 00:02:15,130
Oh, I thought you meant someone special. You really don't know?

18
00:02:15,130 --> 00:02:18,310
He was with the Asia Philharmonic orchestra.

19
00:02:18,310 --> 00:02:21,560
Didn't you come to watch the performance with a colleague?

20
00:02:21,560 --> 00:02:23,970
I think I remember seeing you there.

21
00:02:24,570 --> 00:02:27,980
I actually don't really remember.

22
00:02:27,980 --> 00:02:32,370
Then just forget about it. Why bother trying to remember something you forgot?

23
00:02:32,370 --> 00:02:35,160
It was a pity a brilliant performer passed away like that.

24
00:02:35,160 --> 00:02:39,850
That day was probably his last performance.

25
00:02:44,370 --> 00:02:47,620
To think I've heard his performance before...

26
00:02:50,760 --> 00:02:53,100
Really? That's why I called you.

27
00:02:53,100 --> 00:02:55,230
How is it?

28
00:02:55,230 --> 00:02:57,410
Oh. It's so...

29
00:02:57,410 --> 00:03:02,710
Kim Ian is in the three months of my missing memory.

30
00:03:02,710 --> 00:03:08,010
Is this coincidence, or fate?

31
00:03:10,410 --> 00:03:13,860
Kim Ian. Pianist.

32
00:03:19,480 --> 00:03:22,150
Rising Pianist Kim Ian Dies In Car Accident

33
00:03:27,030 --> 00:03:28,960
No response all day.

34
00:03:28,960 --> 00:03:31,680
No evening calls.

35
00:03:32,960 --> 00:03:34,700
Is he busy?

36
00:03:37,090 --> 00:03:38,780
Kim Ian?

37
00:03:39,480 --> 00:03:43,170
The one you assisted last year?

38
00:03:43,820 --> 00:03:47,690
What? I assisted him?

39
00:03:47,690 --> 00:03:51,700
Why are you so shocked? Maestro Song asked for the favor.

40
00:03:51,700 --> 00:03:55,100
You even went to the airport. You were so annoyed because he was 4-dimensional*.
(Korean slang for eccentric and wacky)

41
00:03:55,100 --> 00:03:57,670
Did you forget about that?

42
00:04:01,400 --> 00:04:04,100
That's insane.

43
00:04:04,100 --> 00:04:07,290
Was it because of the taxi accident last year?

44
00:04:07,290 --> 00:04:10,260
- You said you can barely remember that.
- Yeah.

45
00:04:10,260 --> 00:04:13,100
I think so.

46
00:04:13,100 --> 00:04:16,700
If we think about it, it could be a good thing you forgot.

47
00:04:16,700 --> 00:04:21,390
Someone you knew suddenly passed away. It's unsettling.

48
00:04:22,890 --> 00:04:25,290
I was supposed to go with you that day, but I had a performance.

49
00:04:25,290 --> 00:04:28,400
Of all times, how could our schedules overlap like that?

50
00:04:31,160 --> 00:04:33,110
Seriously?

51
00:04:34,160 --> 00:04:37,790
Ugh. Who has a herniated disc in their twenties?

52
00:04:37,790 --> 00:04:39,900
And my chest is black and blue.

53
00:04:39,900 --> 00:04:43,150
Shouldn't we request compensation for inspectional hazard?

54
00:04:45,670 --> 00:04:47,330
Occupational, occupational hazards!

55
00:04:47,330 --> 00:04:51,030
Hey. It's a total hazard. I should just file a lawsuit.

56
00:04:51,030 --> 00:04:54,990
Go to the hospital after the rehearsal. It could get worse.

57
00:04:54,990 --> 00:04:56,120
Okay.

58
00:04:56,120 --> 00:04:58,960
I'm leaving. Play carefully.

59
00:04:58,960 --> 00:05:00,920
See you.

60
00:05:14,750 --> 00:05:16,270
What's with him?

61
00:05:16,270 --> 00:05:20,550
Did he avoid making eye contact?

62
00:05:26,490 --> 00:05:29,900
What is this? Why did he avoid my eyes?

63
00:05:29,900 --> 00:05:32,030
Did I do something wrong?

64
00:05:32,030 --> 00:05:35,770
No way... is it because I asked for a kiss?

65
00:05:35,770 --> 00:05:38,940
No, no, no. That's not possible.

66
00:05:40,260 --> 00:05:42,510
Then why?

67
00:05:44,480 --> 00:05:47,100
Why do you look so stressed, so early in the morning?

68
00:05:47,100 --> 00:05:50,140
Is Maestro Nam making life difficult for you?

69
00:05:51,160 --> 00:05:53,460
I'll manage to survive.

70
00:05:53,460 --> 00:05:57,140
Being a conductor's assistant isn't easy.

71
00:05:58,100 --> 00:06:00,220
Have you started Michael's lessons, yet?

72
00:06:00,220 --> 00:06:02,730
Not yet. We decided to start next week.

73
00:06:02,730 --> 00:06:06,930
Since you're doing it, make sure to go all the way.

74
00:06:06,930 --> 00:06:11,100
The laws of the jungle apply here as well.

75
00:06:11,100 --> 00:06:12,660
Don't worry.

76
00:06:12,660 --> 00:06:16,630
if I weren't tough, I would be a dead body.

77
00:06:23,590 --> 00:06:25,370
What was that?

78
00:06:33,420 --> 00:06:35,440
Oh my! Oh no.

79
00:06:37,880 --> 00:06:40,420
Principal Wang! It's Ha Eun Ju.

80
00:06:40,420 --> 00:06:43,470
Oh no! Why is she like this?

81
00:06:43,470 --> 00:06:45,550
Is she breathing?

82
00:06:45,550 --> 00:06:46,850
Yes.

83
00:06:46,850 --> 00:06:48,870
Ha Eun Ju? Wake up. Ha Eun Ju?

84
00:06:48,870 --> 00:06:52,630
- What do we do?
- This won't do. Go get Manager Yun.

85
00:06:52,630 --> 00:06:53,900
Yes, ma'am.

86
00:06:53,900 --> 00:06:55,990
Hello? Is this 911?

87
00:06:55,990 --> 00:07:01,550
I Wanna Hear Your Song

88
00:07:15,030 --> 00:07:16,970
When did you wake up?

89
00:07:19,230 --> 00:07:22,240
How are you feeling inside?

90
00:07:22,710 --> 00:07:24,720
What happened?

91
00:07:24,720 --> 00:07:29,800
What do you mean, what happened? Principal Hwang and I found you passed out in the bathroom.

92
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:32,080
Do you know how shocked we were?

93
00:07:34,090 --> 00:07:37,020
What did you tell the company?

94
00:07:37,020 --> 00:07:40,920
Is that what you're worried about? I said you had a cold fever.

95
00:07:40,920 --> 00:07:45,420
So why'd you take that many painkillers? You fell into shock. Are you made of steel?

96
00:07:45,420 --> 00:07:47,690
You even had your stomach pumped, stupid.

97
00:07:47,690 --> 00:07:50,680
Stop overreacting. This is nothing.

98
00:07:50,680 --> 00:07:53,570
Extensor tenosynovitis. (Inflamation of the wrist and hand)

99
00:07:53,570 --> 00:07:57,510
If this is nothing, then what's something?  If you don't treat it right, you can't play for life.

100
00:07:57,510 --> 00:08:00,780
You should rest and receive treatment.

101
00:08:00,780 --> 00:08:05,580
Hey. Do you think I have a carefree life like yours?

102
00:08:05,580 --> 00:08:09,000
If you tell Maestro Nam, I'm going to kill you.

103
00:08:10,090 --> 00:08:13,110
You should leave. I want to be alone.

104
00:08:16,130 --> 00:08:18,660
Sorry I'm the only carefree one.

105
00:08:19,210 --> 00:08:23,120
I'm going to hold onto this for the time being. Keep that in mind.

106
00:08:24,700 --> 00:08:27,360
What's your relationship with Jang Yun?

107
00:08:30,370 --> 00:08:33,630
Why are you asking that out of the blue?

108
00:08:33,630 --> 00:08:35,880
I feel like you two have something going on.

109
00:08:35,880 --> 00:08:39,480
You don't have a good eye for men. It's worrisome.

110
00:08:40,060 --> 00:08:43,470
You just take care of yourself. Don't worry about me.

111
00:09:21,430 --> 00:09:23,970
Returning from the hospital?

112
00:09:23,970 --> 00:09:25,870
Yes.

113
00:09:25,870 --> 00:09:30,230
How is she feeling? Better? There was a lot of talk during rehearsal.

114
00:09:30,230 --> 00:09:33,570
They say it's not the best.

115
00:09:35,470 --> 00:09:38,560
What did you have to tell me? I have to go to my part-time job.

116
00:09:39,860 --> 00:09:42,050
Why do you keep avoiding me?

117
00:09:42,050 --> 00:09:45,340
Me? I didn't do anything of the kind.

118
00:09:45,340 --> 00:09:47,550
Liar.

119
00:09:48,330 --> 00:09:52,670
You ignore my texts and won't look me in the eyes.

120
00:09:52,670 --> 00:09:57,420
I thought about it on the way here, how I should bring it up.

121
00:09:57,420 --> 00:10:01,580
But I'm not going to beat around the bush.

122
00:10:06,250 --> 00:10:12,810
Do you usually ignore women after kissing them?

123
00:10:12,810 --> 00:10:14,600
Ignore?

124
00:10:16,680 --> 00:10:17,330
What?

125
00:10:17,330 --> 00:10:20,220
Don't laugh, I'm being serious.

126
00:10:20,930 --> 00:10:23,170
You approached me first.

127
00:10:23,170 --> 00:10:27,370
You said you wanted to know more about me and that I shouldn't run away.

128
00:10:27,370 --> 00:10:29,680
I'm a very simple person.

129
00:10:29,680 --> 00:10:33,280
If you say that, I think, "Oh really? I should do that."

130
00:10:33,280 --> 00:10:37,140
So, that day too, I just

131
00:10:38,990 --> 00:10:45,370
I went honestly straight... following my heart.

132
00:10:46,170 --> 00:10:52,200
Last time, if you didn't want to kiss me but did it so that I wouldn't be embarrassed,

133
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:56,630
I'm sorry. I was clueless and acted too impulsively.

134
00:10:56,630 --> 00:11:02,600
Also, I think I met Kim Ian.

135
00:11:03,720 --> 00:11:09,170
Jenny  said I briefly assisted him when he was in Korea.

136
00:11:09,170 --> 00:11:12,000
Though I don't remember it.

137
00:11:14,650 --> 00:11:17,900
I wanted to know more about that person.

138
00:11:18,910 --> 00:11:21,110
What does that mean?

139
00:11:22,230 --> 00:11:24,690
I want to remember.

140
00:11:27,450 --> 00:11:29,620
It could be a bad memory.

141
00:11:29,620 --> 00:11:33,940
It could be stressful and horrible.

142
00:11:35,160 --> 00:11:37,470
Is that alright with you?

143
00:11:37,470 --> 00:11:40,320
It could also be good.

144
00:11:41,770 --> 00:11:44,490
You said you don't remember anything.

145
00:11:44,490 --> 00:11:46,380
Yes, I am afraid.

146
00:11:47,490 --> 00:11:50,610
But I'm still going to face it.

147
00:11:50,610 --> 00:11:53,480
Since he's your younger brother.

148
00:11:56,810 --> 00:12:01,410
Also, I want to stop the evening calls.

149
00:12:01,410 --> 00:12:04,530
There's no point discussing about that, because I won't do it.

150
00:12:04,530 --> 00:12:08,930
I don't know what happened between the two of us,

151
00:12:08,930 --> 00:12:12,930
but this is really the end. I'll take my leave.

152
00:12:28,410 --> 00:12:29,560
Hello, Doctor.

153
00:12:29,560 --> 00:12:31,960
I dressed appropriately today.

154
00:12:31,960 --> 00:12:34,080
To see you.

155
00:12:34,810 --> 00:12:38,180
How did you know I worked here?

156
00:12:39,910 --> 00:12:41,520
I heard from Lawyer Lee.

157
00:12:41,520 --> 00:12:43,440
Lawyer Lee Gyeong Su. You remember him, right?

158
00:12:43,440 --> 00:12:47,190
You were supposed to meet him for a blind date but he stood you up.

159
00:12:47,190 --> 00:12:50,800
Stop. Enough about that day.

160
00:12:50,800 --> 00:12:52,860
What is your health concern?

161
00:12:52,860 --> 00:12:55,140
Well, actually, Doctor...

162
00:12:58,040 --> 00:13:02,260
I... am scared of...

163
00:13:03,320 --> 00:13:04,840
circles.

164
00:13:04,840 --> 00:13:05,890
Circles?

165
00:13:05,890 --> 00:13:09,890
Yes. Circles that are clumped together. For instance,

166
00:13:09,890 --> 00:13:15,340
soap bubbles? Frog eggs?

167
00:13:15,340 --> 00:13:17,250
Frog eggs...

168
00:13:17,250 --> 00:13:19,990
Is this a serious disease?

169
00:13:19,990 --> 00:13:21,150
It's trypophobia*.
(literally "fear of holes", sometimes extending to all round shapes)

170
00:13:21,150 --> 00:13:25,380
It's a type of phobia.  Because we don't know the cause, there's no cure for it yet.

171
00:13:25,380 --> 00:13:27,160
For now, I'll prescribe some medicine.

172
00:13:27,160 --> 00:13:29,870
We can find a way to alleviate your phobia slowly.

173
00:13:29,870 --> 00:13:33,290
There's something I have to tell you.

174
00:13:33,290 --> 00:13:35,770
- To me?
- Yes.

175
00:13:37,560 --> 00:13:41,540
It's about a treatment program for autistic children.

176
00:13:43,570 --> 00:13:45,820
You do this kind of work?

177
00:13:47,340 --> 00:13:49,430
I'm unemployed.

178
00:13:50,460 --> 00:13:53,520
I thought I'd have to do something to become close with you.

179
00:13:53,520 --> 00:13:57,020
My name is Choi Gi Sang. My contact info is there.

180
00:13:57,020 --> 00:13:58,840
You'll probably call me.

181
00:13:58,840 --> 00:14:01,710
Then, bye.

182
00:14:05,870 --> 00:14:07,440
My seal and my safe key.

183
00:14:07,440 --> 00:14:08,810
You know the password, right?

184
00:14:08,810 --> 00:14:10,990
Yes.

185
00:14:10,990 --> 00:14:16,890
For the foundation every fiscal quarter, I fly overseas.  I must think about my weeping father.

186
00:14:16,890 --> 00:14:20,480
When I'm not there, what exactly happens to the foundation accounts?

187
00:14:20,480 --> 00:14:23,250
I wouldn't know, I'm nobody.

188
00:14:23,250 --> 00:14:25,990
You would probably say you don't know even if you did

189
00:14:25,990 --> 00:14:29,850
At times like these, I feel shame.

190
00:14:29,850 --> 00:14:33,050
I'm like a  puppet chairwoman.

191
00:14:33,050 --> 00:14:36,040
Instead of just staying in downtown London, you should also go outside of the city.

192
00:14:36,040 --> 00:14:39,590
I heard the Edinburgh summer festival is quite something.

193
00:14:39,590 --> 00:14:40,960
You're changing the topic.

194
00:14:40,960 --> 00:14:43,500
Forget it. How pathetic would it be to go alone?

195
00:14:43,500 --> 00:14:46,500
I almost forgot. Have you made an account?

196
00:14:46,500 --> 00:14:48,980
Professor Kang from the College of Music sent some under borrowed names.

197
00:14:48,980 --> 00:14:51,620
- I thought of using th—
- Kang Myeong Seok?

198
00:14:51,620 --> 00:14:54,270
What is he planning? Don't use it.

199
00:14:54,270 --> 00:14:55,790
I don't want him to know my shortcomings.

200
00:14:55,790 --> 00:14:59,680
He's going to blab about everything to Father!

201
00:14:59,680 --> 00:15:03,210
If you didn't want that, you should've used the company card less.

202
00:15:03,210 --> 00:15:07,140
I don't know what my sister found in him and married him.

203
00:15:07,970 --> 00:15:11,800
He's young. He's six years her junior.

204
00:15:11,800 --> 00:15:15,860
Her standards sure are low. Just like her face.

205
00:15:30,780 --> 00:15:33,150
Are these all the selections?

206
00:15:34,260 --> 00:15:37,610
Gang Sin Yeong is not here.

207
00:15:37,610 --> 00:15:42,220
Why'd you take her out? Because she chewed gum during your lesson?

208
00:15:42,220 --> 00:15:44,710
Is an entrance exam a joke?

209
00:15:44,710 --> 00:15:48,970
If someone like her gets admitted, you'll be stepping in crap, Professor.

210
00:15:50,690 --> 00:15:53,770
Are you worrying for me right now?

211
00:15:53,770 --> 00:15:55,060
Even still.

212
00:15:55,060 --> 00:16:00,140
The Chairwoman's friend's daughter... Her father is a VVIP, a sponsor of our foundation.

213
00:16:00,140 --> 00:16:04,820
You get to do music and eat because of him.

214
00:16:04,820 --> 00:16:09,100
Okay, whatever. I'll deal with Gang Sin Yeong.

215
00:16:09,100 --> 00:16:10,890
Take this.

216
00:16:12,500 --> 00:16:16,580
Take it. It's a bonus, so don't refuse it.

217
00:16:21,980 --> 00:16:24,750
What's with your face?

218
00:16:24,750 --> 00:16:28,240
The flower who plays violin as second chair in the orchestra

219
00:16:28,240 --> 00:16:31,890
looks so stone-faced. Watch your appearance, will you?

220
00:16:31,890 --> 00:16:34,210
Have some meat.

221
00:17:02,590 --> 00:17:06,620
Why are you calling someone out so late at night? Say it over the phone.

222
00:17:06,620 --> 00:17:10,220
So prickly. I just wanted to see your face.

223
00:17:10,220 --> 00:17:11,190
Can't I?

224
00:17:11,190 --> 00:17:13,930
What a thing to say to another man.

225
00:17:14,970 --> 00:17:17,090
What's so urgent?

226
00:17:20,180 --> 00:17:23,110
Yun Yeong Gil is being released.

227
00:17:23,110 --> 00:17:26,270
The truck driver who was responsible for the accident.

228
00:17:26,270 --> 00:17:29,570
What are you talking about? They're still  on appeal. He still has prison time.

229
00:17:29,570 --> 00:17:31,830
He got bail.

230
00:17:33,610 --> 00:17:36,550
He tot bail during the appeal?

231
00:17:37,480 --> 00:17:40,460
- Is that possible?
- Yeah. Though it's rare.

232
00:17:40,460 --> 00:17:43,730
His gambling debts are over 300 million won.

233
00:17:43,730 --> 00:17:47,940
His gambling fees are over 300 million won, so how could he have paid the bail?

234
00:17:47,940 --> 00:17:49,350
I'm wondering if someone paid it for him.

235
00:17:49,350 --> 00:17:50,740
Who?

236
00:17:50,740 --> 00:17:53,200
We have to find out now.

237
00:17:57,700 --> 00:18:02,710
I heard you ignored the CEO's call. He wants to see you in person.

238
00:18:02,710 --> 00:18:04,810
You should meet him.

239
00:18:07,630 --> 00:18:10,510
Let me just ask one thing.

240
00:18:10,510 --> 00:18:15,630
Do you still think that girl could've killed Ian?

241
00:18:31,190 --> 00:18:32,730
Who is it?

242
00:18:34,450 --> 00:18:38,720
Noona, it's me, Jae Hyeong.

243
00:18:38,720 --> 00:18:42,720
What are you doing here? You made my heart drop!

244
00:18:42,720 --> 00:18:46,940
Noona, I've been thinking a lot about what happened.

245
00:18:46,940 --> 00:18:50,460
I've been self-reflecting a lot. I know I did something awful to you.

246
00:18:50,460 --> 00:18:53,920
Can't you give me one more chance?

247
00:18:57,550 --> 00:19:01,140
I don't have a chance to give to you. Go find it somewhere else.

248
00:19:01,140 --> 00:19:03,270
Go home quickly.

249
00:19:05,480 --> 00:19:07,500
Noona.

250
00:19:10,260 --> 00:19:12,000
Wh-wh-what?

251
00:19:13,930 --> 00:19:15,840
Is something wrong?

252
00:19:16,990 --> 00:19:18,760
Noona.

253
00:19:25,270 --> 00:19:28,230
What are you?  Following someone who doesn't like you.

254
00:19:28,230 --> 00:19:30,130
What's with you?

255
00:19:30,130 --> 00:19:35,610
Why do you keep popping up since last time? Are you in some sort of relationship with Noona?

256
00:19:38,040 --> 00:19:40,140
So what if I am?

257
00:19:41,680 --> 00:19:46,880
Noona.  Is what he said true?

258
00:19:46,880 --> 00:19:49,360
In the meantime did you get another guy?

259
00:19:52,600 --> 00:19:57,990
Yes, so don't show up here again. If you do, I'm going mercilessly report you.

260
00:19:57,990 --> 00:20:00,280
Noona.

261
00:20:00,280 --> 00:20:04,330
I said go quickly. You and I are finished. You are the one who ended it.

262
00:20:04,400 --> 00:20:09,800
Noona, Isn't that a little too much? How could you do that to me?

263
00:20:09,800 --> 00:20:12,360
Didn't you hear her say to go?

264
00:20:15,700 --> 00:20:20,700
Noona, I'll call you tomorrow. We'll talk then again.

265
00:20:39,150 --> 00:20:41,020
Are you okay?

266
00:20:41,020 --> 00:20:44,660
If he comes again, don't overlook it. You should report him.

267
00:20:44,660 --> 00:20:47,680
You can't make that kid wake up unless you do that.

268
00:20:55,430 --> 00:20:57,730
He's not that bad.

269
00:20:57,730 --> 00:21:02,770
Just... a little... lacking in common sense.

270
00:21:04,910 --> 00:21:07,580
Because he is naive.

271
00:21:08,210 --> 00:21:12,100
Would a naive person trespass into someone else's home?

272
00:21:12,100 --> 00:21:14,490
Why are you so wishy-washy about him?

273
00:21:14,490 --> 00:21:18,750
That's why, even though he is wrong, you get tangled up with him again.

274
00:21:18,750 --> 00:21:23,240
How can I be colder than this? I used to like him not so long ago.

275
00:21:23,240 --> 00:21:25,990
Would you be able to do that in my place?

276
00:21:25,990 --> 00:21:31,170
Anyway,  even after we kissed, you ignored me.

277
00:21:33,940 --> 00:21:38,680
I'm asking this because I really want to know. What exactly is our relationship?

278
00:21:38,680 --> 00:21:42,520
We kiss and you ignore me and sometimes you pretend to care.

279
00:21:42,520 --> 00:21:44,590
Am I that laughable?

280
00:21:45,530 --> 00:21:47,560
I'm going.

281
00:21:55,890 --> 00:21:58,160
It's not ignoring.

282
00:21:58,160 --> 00:22:00,210
Then what is it?

283
00:22:06,400 --> 00:22:08,610
Want to come with me tomorrow?

284
00:22:10,190 --> 00:22:13,640
- Where to?
- The place where Ian died.

285
00:22:16,150 --> 00:22:18,720
You said you wanted to know.

286
00:22:18,720 --> 00:22:22,120
You said you wanted to remember.  Be responsible for what you said.

287
00:22:41,120 --> 00:22:43,350
"Be responsible for what you said."

288
00:22:44,610 --> 00:22:49,040
He really is mean.

289
00:22:49,040 --> 00:22:51,320
"Be responsible for what you said."

290
00:22:55,670 --> 00:22:58,710
Yu Da.

291
00:23:01,470 --> 00:23:04,820
David vs Goliath. Finally, the war begins.

292
00:23:04,820 --> 00:23:09,130
Who will the Goddess of Victory smile on?

293
00:23:09,200 --> 00:23:12,700
Retract the unfair discharge!  Get enlightened, Sinyeong Philharmonic!

294
00:23:12,700 --> 00:23:16,400
Censure the anti-music tyrant Conductor Nam Ju Wan!

295
00:23:16,450 --> 00:23:18,600
Censure him! Censure him!

296
00:23:18,600 --> 00:23:25,700
Respected Orchestra Members. Everyone, we all can become the victims of unfair discharge.

297
00:23:25,700 --> 00:23:28,810
Please sign the petition to nullify the discharge.

298
00:23:28,810 --> 00:23:30,820
I beg of you.

299
00:23:30,820 --> 00:23:34,760
I really had to gather courage to come here.

300
00:23:34,760 --> 00:23:37,800
Thank you. Thank you.

301
00:23:39,160 --> 00:23:40,730
Help me, please.

302
00:23:40,730 --> 00:23:44,750
I've laid aside my pride and found the courage to come here.

303
00:23:44,750 --> 00:23:46,710
Thank you. Thank you.

304
00:23:46,710 --> 00:23:49,070
Please sign.

305
00:23:49,070 --> 00:23:51,140
Thank you.

306
00:23:51,140 --> 00:23:53,750
What should I do?

307
00:23:54,480 --> 00:23:56,680
What's going on?

308
00:23:56,680 --> 00:23:59,550
Conductor? That is...

309
00:23:59,550 --> 00:24:04,370
Oh? It's the orchesstra member who got  40 points in her performance rating.

310
00:24:05,240 --> 00:24:07,230
That's okay.  Keep on doing what you're doing.

311
00:24:07,230 --> 00:24:10,370
I am a person who respects the freedom of expression.

312
00:24:10,370 --> 00:24:14,250
Even though you are a 40 point-er,  you may continue to express yourself.

313
00:24:14,250 --> 00:24:17,310
Hey! He keeps mentioning the 40 points every time he speaks. 40 points.

314
00:24:17,310 --> 00:24:20,880
Hey, did you do well yourself? How many points did you get as a conductor?

315
00:24:20,880 --> 00:24:23,920
What exactly is the great wrong we did, huh?

316
00:24:23,920 --> 00:24:27,600
She's getting severance pay and extra compensation.  We did everything she asked.

317
00:24:27,600 --> 00:24:30,680
How dare she file a complaint with the Ministry of Labor and stage a protest like that?

318
00:24:30,680 --> 00:24:32,610
It's lucky that the Chairwoman isn't here to see this.

319
00:24:32,610 --> 00:24:37,320
Take a look at this?  What have you done to the organization?

320
00:24:37,320 --> 00:24:40,310
I'm sorry, it's my fault. I'll contact them soon.

321
00:24:40,310 --> 00:24:44,570
What can't a person whose name means future see it?

322
00:24:44,570 --> 00:24:47,920
You must resolve this somehow before the Chairwoman returns. If you die, so do I! Your budget too! Know that.

323
00:24:50,590 --> 00:24:53,530
I don't need a budget.

324
00:24:53,530 --> 00:24:55,890
I'm settling it.

325
00:25:03,430 --> 00:25:05,560
Hello.

326
00:25:07,700 --> 00:25:10,390
Final Programme for Nam Joo Won Inaugural Concert.
Ending Piece: Vitali Chaconne for Violin;  Han Eun Ju is replaced by Jo Han Seok

327
00:25:10,390 --> 00:25:12,990
I heard she went to the hospital yesterday. Is that why she was replaced?

328
00:25:12,990 --> 00:25:16,100
It's Maestro Nam. How are we supposed to know?

329
00:25:18,270 --> 00:25:22,500
You should tell Manager Yun about the last practice outdoors.

330
00:25:22,500 --> 00:25:24,740
Whether its for practice or a performance,

331
00:25:24,740 --> 00:25:28,620
the members should be paid extra pay. How long has this gone on.

332
00:25:28,620 --> 00:25:31,230
You should bring it up first.

333
00:25:31,230 --> 00:25:34,150
You're the one who is tight with Manager Yun.

334
00:25:34,150 --> 00:25:35,870
Do well.

335
00:25:48,850 --> 00:25:52,170
Han Eun Ju is replaced by Jo Han Seok

336
00:26:00,770 --> 00:26:04,590
I've been suffering from jealousy for ten years.

337
00:26:17,630 --> 00:26:20,590
It was you. Did you tell him?

338
00:26:21,570 --> 00:26:25,370
Didn't I tell you I would kill you if you told?

339
00:26:34,670 --> 00:26:36,750
What are you doing?

340
00:26:36,750 --> 00:26:41,910
Don't pick on a newbie. It wasn't her. Go out for a while.

341
00:26:41,910 --> 00:26:43,950
Yes, sir,

342
00:26:48,490 --> 00:26:55,040
Did you think I wouldn't know if I wasn't told?  What arrogance.  I'm not stupid.

343
00:26:55,040 --> 00:27:01,970
I'm certain 9 out of 10 of the members noticed during the last perfromance. Sit out the inaugural concert.  I'm replacing you.

344
00:27:01,970 --> 00:27:03,490
What?

345
00:27:03,490 --> 00:27:06,420
Are you telling me now not to play at all?

346
00:27:06,420 --> 00:27:11,400
I'm telling you for now.  If something goes wrong, you won't be able to play for years.

347
00:27:11,400 --> 00:27:15,360
Are you crazy? I  would rather die.

348
00:27:15,360 --> 00:27:19,080
I know my symptoms best.

349
00:27:21,650 --> 00:27:23,870
If you've said all you have to say, leave.

350
00:27:43,650 --> 00:27:45,990
It's ready.

351
00:27:50,300 --> 00:27:55,850
I was hoping you would select a white chrysanthemus.  Anyhow, I thought it wasn't for condolences, so I wrapped it.

352
00:27:55,850 --> 00:27:57,930
I wasn't sure what you liked.

353
00:27:57,930 --> 00:27:59,960
I like it. Thank you.

354
00:27:59,960 --> 00:28:01,780
Keep up the good work!

355
00:28:05,280 --> 00:28:09,200
Well, he is the handsome child of some family.

356
00:28:11,290 --> 00:28:13,210
What are you looking at with that smile on your face?

357
00:28:13,210 --> 00:28:16,420
What is there to look at?  I was smiling just looking at him.

358
00:28:16,420 --> 00:28:20,700
If I too had one handsome son, I would not want anything else.

359
00:28:20,700 --> 00:28:23,400
The new song of the traditional song...

360
00:28:24,850 --> 00:28:26,960
It is a death anniversary?

361
00:28:26,960 --> 00:28:31,370
Why didn't you tell me in advance? My clothes are a mess and my face...

362
00:28:31,370 --> 00:28:36,380
What does your face matter.  What do the dead know?

363
00:28:36,380 --> 00:28:38,510
They know everything.

364
00:28:38,510 --> 00:28:41,850
They see it all from heaven.
